com.hazelcast.hotrestart

Class NoOpHotRestartService

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.hotrestart.NoOpHotRestartService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HotRestartService

    public class NoOpHotRestartService
extends Object
implements HotRestartService
    Empty implementation of HotRestartService to avoid null checks. This will provide default behaviour when hot restart is not available or not enabled.

    • Method Detail

      • backup

        public void backup()
        Description copied from interface: HotRestartService
        Attempts to perform a cluster hot restart data backup. Each node will create a directory under the defined backup dir with the name HotRestartService.BACKUP_DIR_PREFIX followed by the cluster time defined by this node. The backup request is performed transactionally. This method will throw an exception if an another request (transaction) is already in progress. If a node is already performing a backup (there is a file indicating a backup is in progress), the node will only log a warning and ignore the backup request.
        Specified by:
        backup in interface HotRestartService

      • backup

        public void backup(long backupSeq)
        Description copied from interface: HotRestartService
        Attempts to perform a cluster hot restart data backup. Each node will create a directory under the defined backup dir with the name HotRestartService.BACKUP_DIR_PREFIX followed by the backupSeq. The backup request is performed transactionally. This method will throw an exception if an another request (transaction) is already in progress. If a node is already performing a backup (there is a file indicating a backup is in progress), the node will only log a warning and ignore the backup request.
        Specified by:
        backup in interface HotRestartService
        Parameters:
        backupSeq - the suffix of the backup directory for this cluster hot restart backup
